meta {
  name: Train Model (per company)
  type: http
  seq: 2
}

post {
  url: http://localhost:8090/train/{{company_id}}
  body: none
  auth: none
}

vars:pre-request {
  company_id: 00000000-a1c0-deb0-0000-000000000001
}

docs {
  Trains (or retrains) a fraud detection model for the given company.

  The Rust service pulls all labeled transactions from the foundry DB for this
  company. Labels are derived from:
    - alert.status = 'resolved'           -> fraud
    - vendor has critical finding         -> fraud
    - alert.status = 'false_positive'     -> not fraud
    - everything else                      -> unlabeled (skipped from training)

  Requires at least 30 labeled samples with both classes present, otherwise
  returns 400 with an error message.

  Response (200):
  {
    "company_id": "uuid",
    "samples_trained": 320,
    "accuracy": 0.94,
    "trained_at": "2026-04-11T22:30:00Z"
  }

  Response (400):
  {
    "error": "not enough labeled data, need at least 30"
  }

  The default company_id (00000000-a1c0-deb0-0000-000000000001) is the
  AI Playground Co created by the seed-playground-data binary in the
  ai-triage-agent repo. Override the var if you're training a real company.

  This is the endpoint the nightly retrain cron should hit.
}